[{"_path":"/blog/is-nuxt3-ready","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_empty":false,"title":"Is Nuxt 3 Ready is being archived","description":"Archiving this pet project in favor of the official site","excerpt":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Last week, with the recent open beta of Nuxt 3, I decided to build \"Is Nuxt 3 Ready\", that esentially listed the compatibility of Nuxt modules. Initially, it was just a pet project to play with the new Nuxt 3 features, but after "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://twitter.com/dawntraoz/status/1451904601989566464","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a tweet from @Dawntraoz"}]},{"type":"text","value":" it got really popular. I revamped the design, made it easier for others to contribute and added really nice features such as sorting by status or light/dark modes."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Today, at the time of writing, Nuxt finally added compatibility support. They let me know via "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/owlnai/isnuxt3ready/issues/17","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a GitHub Issue"}]},{"type":"text","value":" so I could use their DB to fetch the info instead of having an inline JSON but I decided it was better to archive the repository."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why? As a former Wiki Manager at Fandom, and user for more than a decade, I've witnessed the side effects of maintaining two different sites with the same scope. I'm not saying forking it's a bad thing, but I strongly believe code is a team effort, and joining forces benefits the Nuxt community more than keeping two separate projects that look nearly the same."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'll make a few changes to the repository to announce the migration and keep the site up for some time before redirecting it to the official modules site. I'm really thankful for all the support this pet project received, specially to those who contributed to it or promoted it. I have some things planned so you'll hear more from me soon."}]}]},"tag":"development","date":1635368278138,"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Last week, with the recent open beta of Nuxt 3, I decided to build \"Is Nuxt 3 Ready\", that esentially listed the compatibility of Nuxt modules. Initially, it was just a pet project to play with the new Nuxt 3 features, but after "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://twitter.com/dawntraoz/status/1451904601989566464","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a tweet from @Dawntraoz"}]},{"type":"text","value":" it got really popular. I revamped the design, made it easier for others to contribute and added really nice features such as sorting by status or light/dark modes."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Today, at the time of writing, Nuxt finally added compatibility support. They let me know via "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/owlnai/isnuxt3ready/issues/17","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a GitHub Issue"}]},{"type":"text","value":" so I could use their DB to fetch the info instead of having an inline JSON but I decided it was better to archive the repository."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why? As a former Wiki Manager at Fandom, and user for more than a decade, I've witnessed the side effects of maintaining two different sites with the same scope. I'm not saying forking it's a bad thing, but I strongly believe code is a team effort, and joining forces benefits the Nuxt community more than keeping two separate projects that look nearly the same."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'll make a few changes to the repository to announce the migration and keep the site up for some time before redirecting it to the official modules site. I'm really thankful for all the support this pet project received, specially to those who contributed to it or promoted it. I have some things planned so you'll hear more from me soon."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:is-nuxt3-ready.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/is-nuxt3-ready.md","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/blog/new-site","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_empty":false,"title":"Refactoring my personal site for the nth time","description":"Why I decided to re-do my site and how.","excerpt":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I've been building websites for a decade, but there's one thing that I never got right: my personal website. A personal website is a reflection of your brand, what you want to show to other people."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"why-building-a-new-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why building a new site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I think every web developer who has been in the industry for a while has felt the need to redesign their portfolio. Either because they want to implement new ideas they've just learned or they just want to get their hands into coding. Either way, I really enjoy building stuff and I was happy to work on this."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"rebuilding-the-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rebuilding the site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"designing-the-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Designing the site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Every time I open Figma, in order to improve my skills and abilities, I try to create my best work so far. I believe that's a good way to surpass your limits and get out of your confort zone."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After some time looking for design inspiration on the Internet and world-class portfolios, I got a few ideas to implement."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"Early Figma prototype of the site","src":"/blog/figma.png"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A prototype doesn't need to be pixel-perfect and the accurate final representation, but rather a playground to test your ideas and evolve."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"implementing-the-idea"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Implementing the idea"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now it was time to make the idea come to life. I decided to go with Nuxt and UnoCSS since they're tipically my favorite stack to work with. After spending a weekend, the page was nearly finished. I made some changes compared to the Figma file above, which you should notice if you go to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"homepage"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After getting everything to work, it was time to polish it. I ran multiple Lighthouse audits as well as my own testing using DevTools and while I got 100/100/100/100 scores, there was room for improvement, so I spent hours optimizing font files, testing on multiple screens and devices...until it was good to go."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"hosting-it"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hosting it"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now it comes the fun part. Setting up the domain and making it available to the rest of the world. I chose Netlify as I've been their customer and user for years, and they were already managing the namespace of my domain for certain tools and even my own link shortener. At the time of publishing this blog, I'll have open-sourced it if you want to take a look at it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"hr","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm really happy with how fast the site was finished, and my friends liked the result. Got any comments or questions? Feel free to "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/contact"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"contact me"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]}]},"tag":"development","date":1631138400000,"updated":1655980885868,"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I've been building websites for a decade, but there's one thing that I never got right: my personal website. A personal website is a reflection of your brand, what you want to show to other people."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"why-building-a-new-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why building a new site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I think every web developer who has been in the industry for a while has felt the need to redesign their portfolio. Either because they want to implement new ideas they've just learned or they just want to get their hands into coding. Either way, I really enjoy building stuff and I was happy to work on this."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"rebuilding-the-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rebuilding the site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"designing-the-site"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Designing the site"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Every time I open Figma, in order to improve my skills and abilities, I try to create my best work so far. I believe that's a good way to surpass your limits and get out of your confort zone."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After some time looking for design inspiration on the Internet and world-class portfolios, I got a few ideas to implement."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"Early Figma prototype of the site","src":"/blog/figma.png"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A prototype doesn't need to be pixel-perfect and the accurate final representation, but rather a playground to test your ideas and evolve."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"implementing-the-idea"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Implementing the idea"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now it was time to make the idea come to life. I decided to go with Nuxt and UnoCSS since they're tipically my favorite stack to work with. After spending a weekend, the page was nearly finished. I made some changes compared to the Figma file above, which you should notice if you go to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"homepage"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After getting everything to work, it was time to polish it. I ran multiple Lighthouse audits as well as my own testing using DevTools and while I got 100/100/100/100 scores, there was room for improvement, so I spent hours optimizing font files, testing on multiple screens and devices...until it was good to go."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"hosting-it"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hosting it"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now it comes the fun part. Setting up the domain and making it available to the rest of the world. I chose Netlify as I've been their customer and user for years, and they were already managing the namespace of my domain for certain tools and even my own link shortener. At the time of publishing this blog, I'll have open-sourced it if you want to take a look at it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"hr","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm really happy with how fast the site was finished, and my friends liked the result. Got any comments or questions? Feel free to "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/contact"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"contact me"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"why-building-a-new-site","depth":2,"text":"Why building a new site"},{"id":"rebuilding-the-site","depth":2,"text":"Rebuilding the site","children":[{"id":"designing-the-site","depth":3,"text":"Designing the site"},{"id":"implementing-the-idea","depth":3,"text":"Implementing the idea"},{"id":"hosting-it","depth":3,"text":"Hosting it"}]}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:new-site.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/new-site.md","_extension":"md","coverImage":"/blog/figma.png"},{"_path":"/blog/your-own-shortener","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_empty":false,"title":"Your own link shortener","description":"Discover how to create short links paired with your domain.","excerpt":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You surely have heard of link shorteners. Be it "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"bit.ly"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"t.co"}]},{"type":"text","value":" or "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"aka.ms"}]},{"type":"text","value":" they're everywhere."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"They exist for branding purposes, creating convenient short links for really long URLs or just having a place to quickly share stuff between devices without having to store it elsewhere."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But how do I get one? There's a tool for that!"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"netlify-shortener"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"netlify-shortener"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"overview"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Overview"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kent C. Dodds created "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/kentcdodds/netlify-shortener","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"an interesting tool"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on GitHub that lets you create short links with a simple console command. While it was made for Netlify, it could be adapted to other sites like Vercel or you could just write a simple Nginx rule if you got a VPS."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The explanation of this tool is quite simple. It leverages Netlify's built-in redirect system to create a custom route and take you to the desired external address. Then it auto-commits and pushes your code to the remote Git repository (e.g Github)."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you have your Netlify site connected to the repo, it will trigger a new build, making your short link available to the world in a few seconds."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"getting-it-to-work"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Getting it to work"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first step is forking the repo and then setting up the Netlify site. Then just sync both. You don't need any paid Netlify features or complex setup."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then clone the repo locally. Not strictly necessary, but I personally recommend to "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"npm link"}]},{"type":"text","value":" the folder after cloning the repo. This will make the locally installed package available everywhere in your PC, allowing you to just run the CLI command and automatically doing the rest, even if you're not in that folder."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"trying-it-out"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Trying it out"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you named the linked binary \"shorten\":"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"shorten https://example.com"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"will yield a random short string. Just like typical shorteners do."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"shorten https://example.com ohwow"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"will yield a "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"mydomain.com/ohwow"}]},{"type":"text","value":" as the short link, meaning that we can customize the short string if we needed a memorable name."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"next-steps"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next steps"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now, this is pretty great as it's probably the easiest method of having a self-hosted link shortener, but if you want the fancy web UI there are some interesting ideas."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inspired by NetlifyCMS, you could leverage their Git Gateway to \"push\" the commit containing the new redirect rules using a simple API."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I don't know if anyone else has tried it out yet, but it's certainly a good side project for the weekends."}]}]},"tag":"development","date":1634839479350,"updated":1655980885868,"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You surely have heard of link shorteners. Be it "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"bit.ly"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"t.co"}]},{"type":"text","value":" or "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"aka.ms"}]},{"type":"text","value":" they're everywhere."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"They exist for branding purposes, creating convenient short links for really long URLs or just having a place to quickly share stuff between devices without having to store it elsewhere."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"But how do I get one? There's a tool for that!"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"netlify-shortener"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"netlify-shortener"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"overview"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Overview"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kent C. Dodds created "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/kentcdodd